ly if it has a high amount of grease.";i:14;s:66:"Proper maintenance is essential for the door to function properly.";i:15;s:34:"Metal Pieces Contracts and Shrink.";i:16;s:117:"Another reason that your garage door wont open all the way in cold weather is probably that the metal has contracted.";i:17;s:81:"In cold temperature the space between molecules reduces making the metal shrinks.";i:18;s:111:"My garage door has two sensors either of which can cause the door to open immediately after apparently closing.";i:19;s:176:"A force-sensitive switch that detects if the motor torque is excessive typically tripped by incorrect adjustment or by leaving a solid object in the way of the descending door.";i:20;s:246:"The first thing youll want to do when your garage door opens a little and then stops is to check to see if there is anything obstructing the lensesYour garage door will immediately stop and close if anything is in the field of view of the lenses.";i:21;s:38:"My garage door wont close all the way.";i:22;s:46:"It goes part of the way down and then back up.";i:23;s:104:"Sometimes it doesnt go down much at all and sometimes it goes almost half way down before going back up.";i:24;s:80:"There is nothing between the sensors that would cause it to trigger then sensor.";i:25;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than closed and the garage door opener is activated the door will close.";i:26;s:144:"If the garage door makes contact with an obstruction while closing the door will reverse the opener will beep and the lights will flash 5 times.";i:27;s:163:"With the door closed unhook the trolley from the door and see if the trolley without the door will go open then close the whole way without tripping and reversing.";i:28;s:151:"There are a couple of things that would reverse the door and open it back up but usually the lights flashing the ten times is the sensors were tripped.";i:29;s:92:"If the door hits the floor before the closed limit switch stops power to the motor the door.";i:30;s:54:"Open the garage door and watch it closely as it opens.";i:31;s:118:"When the garage door opens about halfway or 5 feet from the ground and stops the up limit switch needs to be adjusted.";i:32;s:157:"My garage door closes most of the way then goes back up again On Sectional doors- The most common reason I see for this situation is binding torsion springs.";i:33;s:114:"If you havent had your door properly serviced in a long time than your springs may have a buildup of surface rust.";i:34;s:87:"Quite often the cause of your doors malfunction is an improperly set garage door limit.";i:35;s:106:"This requires a simple turn with a screwdriver to reset the limit so the garage door opens and closes all.";i:36;s:102:"Its the same sort of Craftsman garage door opener that most of suburbia has here in the United States.";i:37;s:169:"This morning I found the garage door open after my wife left in the morning and I found that it was because the door is currently closing all of the way then re-opening.";i:38;s:106:"First of all you need to diagnose the issue and discover whats stopping the door from opening all the way.";i:39;s:113:"To determine if the root cause is the automatic opener or the garage door itself follow these three simple steps.";i:40;s:26:"Close the door completely.";i:41;s:78:"Pull the emergency release cord to disengage the opener trolley from the door.";i:42;s:191:"When a garage door descends on command but then immediately reverses itself the problem is usually with the sensor eyes along the side tracks or with the doors wheels binding in their tracks.";i:43;s:146:"But when the door begins to descend all on its own the problem may point to the openers logic board or the circuitry inside the motor unit itself.";i:44;s:38:"Genie Garage Door Opener doesnt close.";i:45;s:47:"Genie garage door opens fine but does not shut.";i:46;s:45:"Garage door closes a little and back returns.";i:47;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than 